<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-08-16T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-08-16T04:00:00-05:00" n="466" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 Ic/17: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ruddock</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-16T17:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">August 16,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 16—10:53
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>288. Your 222, August 9th, 4 p.m. Diplomatic corps desires to make
                            warning against future mutiny general and not limited Ichang. I am
                            assenting.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ruddock</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>